Manchester City manager, Pep Guardiola has named a strong squad to tackle Arsenal in today’s away Premier League fixture at the Emirates Stadium. Guardiola released a list of 18 players to take on Arsenal, according to Manchester Evening News. Man City head to the game following a 2-1 defeat to Manchester United in their last Premier League encounter. Below is Man City’s travelling squad against Arsenal: Goalkeepers: Ederson, Carson Defenders: Walker, Cancelo, Otamendi, Garcia, Mendy, Zinchenko, Angelino Midfielders: Rodri, Fernandinho, De Bruyne, Foden, Gundogan Forwards: Jesus, Bernardo, Sterling, Mahrez The kick-off time for the match is 5:30pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.